  "title": "The World's Loudest Shout Belongs to a Town Crier Named Lord Joseph",
  "script": "122 decibels — by yelling? Joseph McGrail-Bateup is the official town crier for Canberra and Queanbeyan, Australia — and now the loudest shouter on Earth. He set the Guinness World Record for loudest shout by a male individual, clocking 122.4 decibels. That is rock-concert volume. Actually louder than a military jet taking off. The man is a living foghorn. Here's the twist: Joseph grew up as the quiet kid. Genuinely shy. Never the loudest in the room. He became a town crier in 2017, started competing in championships in 2022, and in May he opened his mouth and beat everyone. His official title is Lord Joseph. He is the loudest person alive. So: how does the quiet kid become the record-holder?",
